uk.org.taverna.scufl2.xml.t2flow.jaxb

Class Link

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.org.taverna.scufl2.xml.t2flow.jaxb.Link

  • public class Link
extends Object
    One end of the links in the Datalink. A link goes from/to a port, either a dataflow port or a processor port. If the type is "dataflow", then the "processor" element must not be present, and the port defines a dataflow input (if this link is a source) or output port (if this link is a sink). The must not be more than one DataLink with a sink to the same dataflow output port. If the type is "processor", then the "processor" element must be present, and name a processor in the same dataflow. The port must name a defined processor input port (if this link is a sink) or processor output port (if this link is a source). There must not be more than one DataLink with a sink to the same processor input port. If the type is "merge", this link must be used as a source (merge can't be used with a sink), and is similar to the type of "processor", except that more than one link to the processor is allowed. A "merge" element will be inserted in front of the defined processor input port, and the incoming links will be added to the merge in the order they have been defined in the dataflow.
